verbs.description: unpaste (third-person singular simple present unpastes, present participle unpasting, simple past and past participle unpasted)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove or take down (something pasted); to unstick.
examples: […]  He took away the frame itself, as well as the notice.Mr. MacCulloch. I recollect Mr. Dobrée stating that his reason for taking the cadre was, that the notice was pasted, and that he could not unpaste it.
